# CentralSquare Document Branding Reference

## Color Constants

Use these exact values across all documents for brand consistency.

```javascript
// Primary brand
const CS_DARK = "1E2A3A";       // Dark chrome — table headers, title text
const CS_ORANGE = "ED591F";     // Dispatch Orange — accents, section dividers, CTAs
const CS_GRAY = "333333";       // Body text
const CS_MID_GRAY = "666666";   // Secondary text, footer, labels
const CS_LIGHT_GRAY = "F0F2F5"; // Metadata cell backgrounds, section bars
const CS_BORDER = "CCCCCC";     // Table borders, divider lines
const CS_ACCENT_BG = "FFF0EB";  // Light orange — recommended option highlight, callout boxes

// Functional
const CS_BLUE = "2A7BC8";       // Links, informational accents
const CS_GREEN = "1B7A3D";      // Positive assessment text
const CS_GREEN_BG = "E8F5E9";   // Do's column, positive highlights
const CS_RED_TEXT = "C62828";    // Negative/warning text
const CS_RED_BG = "FFEBEE";     // Don'ts column, negative highlights
const CS_WARN_BG = "FFF3CD";    // Caution assessment cells
```

## Shared Styling Primitives

These are used across all document types:

```javascript
const border = { style: BorderStyle.SINGLE, size: 1, color: CS_BORDER };
const borders = { top: border, bottom: border, left: border, right: border };
const cellMargins = { top: 80, bottom: 80, left: 120, right: 120 };

const headerCellShading = { fill: CS_DARK, type: ShadingType.CLEAR };
const accentCellShading = { fill: CS_ACCENT_BG, type: ShadingType.CLEAR };
const lightCellShading = { fill: CS_LIGHT_GRAY, type: ShadingType.CLEAR };
const warnCellShading = { fill: CS_WARN_BG, type: ShadingType.CLEAR };
```

